President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Deborah L. Birx as Ambassador at Large and Coordinator of United States Government Activities to Combat HIV/AIDS Globally at the Department of State. Dr. Birx is the Director of the Division of Global HIV/AIDS at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). She has extensive experience in the field, having served as the Director of CDC's Global AIDS Programs and in various positions in the U.S. Army. President Obama also intends to nominate Suzette Kimball as Director of the United States Geological Survey at the Department of the Interior. Dr. Kimball has been the Deputy Director of the USGS since 2010 and has fulfilled the duties of the Director since February 2013. Lastly, President Obama intends to appoint Jerilyn Mendoza as a member of the Joint Public Advisory Committee of the Commission for Environmental Cooperation. Ms. Mendoza is currently the Senior Environmental Affairs Program Manager at the Southern California Gas Company and has previously served in various environmental positions in California.